    <abstract>Lu Yin has an entry on "The record of the Stele by Luo Cheng at the Jade Emperor Hall
        from Ming dynasty, at Mount Jiliang". Mount Jiliang is the old name for Mount Sili. Lu Yin
        goes on to comment: "The writing is all vulgar, and does not seem to have come from the
        brush of an eminent person." </abstract>
